# .hushlogin -- tell login to stfu
#
#   @author     Pat Gaffney <pat@hypepat.com>
#   @created    2016-09-18
#   @modified   2016-09-18
#
#   The very *presence* of this file tells login(1) to forget about
#   displaying the copyright notice, date and time of last login, 
#   message of the day, etc.
#
#   The same *hushed* functionality can be accomplished by passing
#   the -q option to login(1) -- but this file is easier.
#
#   If the system supports a message of the day, it can be found in
#   /etc/motd.
#
#####################################################################